   "source": [
    "\n",
    "### Six PIllars of OOPS\n",
    "- Class - BluePrint of an object\n",
    "- Object - Real world entity\n",
    "- Inheritance\n",
    "- Encapsulation\n",
    "- Abstraction\n",
    "- Polymorphism"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "08ea6d5f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Example: Car \n",
    "1-> properties -- Data (variable) color, brand, speed\n",
    "2-> Behaviours -- (Functions) start(), acceerate(), break()\n",
    "\n",
    "In OOPS:\n",
    "    Car -> Class\n",
    "    Specific Car -> object\n",
    "\n",
    "    Classs -> student\n",
    "    Object -> prateek, rimshi\n",
    "\n",
    "special Meathod: __init__()\n",
    "This is called a constructor.\n",
    "It initializes object data.\n",
    "Constricutor automatically gets called when object is created"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "id": "37d1b457",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Student Name: Rimshi\n",
      "\n",
      "Student Name: Ankit\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "class Student:\n",
    "    role = \"Student\" # Class Attribute\n",
    "\n",
    "    def __init__(self, name, marks): # self refers to current object\n",
    "        self.name = name #instance attribute\n",
    "        self.marks = marks #instance attribute\n",
    "\n",
    "    def display(self,):\n",
    "        print(\"Student Name:\", self.name)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Class attributes are generalised for each object\n",
    "# Instance attribute values are specific to that perticular object\n",
    "s1 = Student(\"Rimshi\", 90)\n",
    "s2 = Student(\"Ankit\", 85)\n",
    "\n",
    "s1.display()\n",
    "print()\n",
    "s2.display()\n",
    "print()\n"
   ]
  },
